From fe4d4a4ffa4eadf25170f9fda36cd9c40449d285 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: rcorex <218065218+rcorex@users.noreply.github.com>
Date: Thu, 2 Apr 2026 16:23:30 +0700
Subject: [PATCH] Webos ac3 eac3 dialnorm bypass and optimizations (#70)

* Webos ac3 eac3 dialnorm defeat and audio pipeline optimizations

* Replace synchronous `CSettings` queries in processing loops with atomic variables updated via `ISettingCallback`
* Fix lock-contention and performance degradation issues inside `ProcessAudio`, `SetupAudio`, and `SetupBitstreamConverter`
* Defeat Dialog Normalization for AC3 EAC3

In AC3 or EAC3 audio, the dialnorm (Dialog Normalization) metadata embedded in the stream causes the decoder to attenuate the volume.
This change overrides the 5-bit dialnorm property in the Bit Stream Information (BSI) header to `11111` (decimal 31) for both AC3 and EAC3 streams before it is sent to pass-through or decoded.
